summaries.short: Season Three Premiere. Selina courts caucus voters in Iowa amidst rumors that could affect the next election.
summaries.full: Season Three Premiere. In Iowa, Selina courts possible caucus voters at a book signing for her new autobiography, while her team is in D.C. attending a staff wedding. As the day proceeds, Selina and her staff get word of a rumor that could affect the next election.

summaries.short: Selina is forced to reexamine her stance on a major issue; Gary questions his role; Jonah starts a blog.
summaries.full: After a quick visit to their new campaign HQ, Selina and her team go on a ride-along with the Coast Guard, where they learn the president has flipped on a major issue--which makes Selina reexamine her stance. Meanwhile, Gary questions his role with the Veep, and Jonah's new political blog causes trouble.

summaries.short: (Season Two Finale) With the administration in full crisis mode and Selina's future in doubt, the entire staff goes on frenzied job hunt.

summaries.short: Selina has a memorable fundraising trip to Silicon Valley; Jonah makes a viral video; Dan starts a rumor against Chung.
summaries.full: On a fundraising trip in Silicon Valley, Selina is challenged by an anti-fracking mom and visits the campus of Clovis, a tech company with a young, ambitious CEO. Back in D.C., Jonah makes a crude viral video of the Selina/mom encounter, and Dan, with Ben's help, gets an idea for a rumor he can spread against Chung.
